Detectives are "hard at work" to gather clues after six females were shot dead in a home in Philippi East, Cape Town, Western Cape, police said on Saturday. The women, aged 18 to 26, were attacked in Marcus Garvey at around 22:55 on Friday by unknown suspects, said Captain FC van Wyk. "The motive for the murders is unknown at this stage. The circumstances surrounding the incident are being investigated and more information cannot be released at this stage," he said. No one has been arrested.